article.description: Glenn Sanabria had a season-high 25 points as St. Francis Brooklyn defeated Central Connecticut 90-79 on Saturday. Rosel Hurley added 20 points for the Terriers.
article.headline: St. Francis Brooklyn beats Central Connecticut 90-79
article.linkText: St. Francis Brooklyn beats Central Connecticut 90-79
article.story: BROOKLYN HEIGHTS, N.Y. -- Glenn Sanabria had a season-high 25 points as St. Francis Brooklyn defeated Central Connecticut 90-79 on Saturday. Rosel Hurley added 20 points for the Terriers. Jalen Jordan had 13 points for St. Francis (16-11, 8-6 Northeast Conference). Deniz Celen added 12 points and seven rebounds. St. Francis put up 58 points in the second half, a season high for the team. Tyler Kohl had 26 points and 10 rebounds for the Blue Devils (11-16, 5-9). Jamir Coleman added 17 points. Joe Hugley had 16 points. The Terriers leveled the season series against the Blue Devils with the win. Central Connecticut defeated St. Francis 78-72 on Jan. 31. St. Francis Brooklyn matches up against St. Francis (Pa.) on the road on Thursday. Central Connecticut matches up against Mount St. Mary's at home on Thursday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
